<br>
Anyway, here are the new Calendar rules:<br>
<br>
1) You can only have 3 active raids on the Calendar at one time, once the date of the 1st event has come and gone you can post another.<br>
<br>
2) These events can all be on the week-end, BUT, you must rotate the days, i.e. One on friday, one on the sunday of the next week, one on the saturday of the week after that.<br>
<br>
3) Gods are treated like rare drops, if it happens to be up on the day you are scheduled, you got lucky.<br>
<br>
4) There can only be 4 open raids on Hate, and 4 open raids on Fear per month. (Open raids are raids hosted by individuals, not guilds)<br>
<br>
5) Open raids CAN NEVER be changed to a guild raid.<br>
<br>
6) You must be out of a plane 13 hours after the time you had posted for the event to start. (i.e. Event is at 7pm PST, you MUST be out by 8am PST, this gives you 1hour for drop in and set-up and 12 hours to clear the zone).(Please note, some guilds may plan some 4am PST raids, this will still allow 3 raids on the week-ends, one at 4am PST Sat. One at 5pm PST sat, and one at 6am PST Sunday. Please take note when posting an event)<br>
<br>
7) Events are to be scheduled in a PST format (Verant's time), however, be nice and do the conversions so other time zones will know.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  PoG can hold more than one raid at a time, if you would like to host a raid the same time someone else is, please make sure the leader is ok by it. If you are going for a specific MOB in PoG, please point that out in your post.<br>
<br>
9) Dragons and MOBs are going to be done on a list basis. If it is your turn to kill it, you have 48 hours to kill it and then it becomes fair game to anyone else that wishes to and you must put yourself back at the bottom of the list. (I have sent an Email to Bish to see if there is an easy way to organize this).<br>
<br>
We are in the process of formulating a list of MOBs that need to be on the list basis. These will include triggered, long spawns, etc.<br>
<br>
There may be a couple more, I have to double check the log.<br>
<br>
Please, everyone follow these rules, for if done they will help to ease the stress and fights on the server and allow us to keep it peaceful. Please E-mail me at Nairb000@hotmail.com, or Bish, or Milynna for more info.<br>
<br>
Lastly, we would like to ask, that each Guild (especially those represented at the meeting) post an agreement post (like a contract) after this, to state that you are in agreement. If you were not at the Meeting and do not like the rules, please follow them until the next meeting and come so you will have a voice. This is done to form an actual Council of Guilds that will have an active voice in the way that we can keep this server peaceful. <br>
